---
layout: layouts/base.njk
active: manual
title: "The Manual — Container Desktop setup guides for Podman, Docker & Apple™ Container"
description: "Set up Podman, Docker and Apple™ Container on Linux, macOS and Windows — native, virtualized, colima/LIMA or WSL. Every command, copy-paste ready."
---
<div class="wrap">
  <div class="mhero">
    <div class="eyebrow">Handbook · bring your own engine</div>
    <h1>The Manual</h1>
    <p>Set up Podman, Docker and Apple™ Container on any platform — local, virtualized, or WSL. Every command, every engine, copy-paste ready.</p>
    <div class="osjump">
      {%- for g in collections.guides %}<a href="#{{ g.data.os }}"><i class="{{ g.data.iconClass or 'fab' }} {{ g.data.osIcon }}"></i> {{ g.data.osLabel }}</a>{% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="shell">
    <aside class="side">
      {%- for g in collections.guides %}
      <div class="grp"><i class="{{ g.data.iconClass or 'fab' }} {{ g.data.osIcon }}"></i> {{ g.data.osLabel }}</div>
      {%- for s in g.data.sections %}<a href="#{{ s.id }}">{{ s.label }}</a>{% endfor %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </aside>

    <main class="content">
      {%- for g in collections.guides %}
      <div class="guide-os" id="{{ g.data.os }}"><i class="{{ g.data.iconClass or 'fab' }} {{ g.data.osIcon }}"></i><h2>{{ g.data.osLabel }}</h2></div>
      {{ g.templateContent | safe }}
      {%- endfor %}
    </main>
  </div>
</div>
